description: Aiming for a high score on your American History SAT II?  Look no further!  Upward Mobility's SAT II U.S. History Exam Prep app for Palm webOS is the perfect tool to help students properly prepare for this competitive college entrance test.  *  The module covers the founding of the New World up through the Bill Clinton administration, with 150 realistic questions that address nearly all the topics commonly found on the exam.  *  Each question is followed by a clear and thoughtful explanation, paired with a Key Takeaway that summarizes the key learning point of the question, ensuring comprehensive understanding of the material. Whether you are taking the test for the first time, or striving to improve your score, this app will be a useful component of your test preparation.  *  Upward Mobility provides a wide range of AP, SAT, and CLEP Exam Prep apps to help you achieve your college entrance goals.   ||  Katie McConnaughey is a freelance writer and editor based in Redmond, Washington. She received her BA in History from Mount Holyoke College in 2004.  *  Since that time, she has worked in the publishing industry, primarily on children's and YA  literature. Since going freelance in 2007, Katie has edited, written, proofread, and copyedited for a large variety of clients, including Simon & Schuster, Alloy Entertainment, becker&mayer! book producers, Symphony Space, diacriTech, the NYC Department of Health & Mental Hygiene, and a number of private clients.  ||  Upward Mobility creates high quality management education and test preparation material that is witty, engaging, and adds value in the learning process.  We hire only expert writers who have strong knowledge in the subject matter and put all of our materials through a thorough review process.  *   We are a double bottom line company committed to education in the developing world. Some of the profits will be used to deploy education via mobile phone in emerging countries.
